               <msContents>
                  <summary>A Persian commentary by Khalīl Ibn al-Ghāzī al-Qazvīnī of <title>Kitāb al-ṣalawāt</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa">کتاب الصلوةکتاب الصلوة</title> the eleventh book of the great work on religious law of the Shi’ite traditions <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc">Usūl al-Kāfī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar">اصول الكافي</title> ، by <name ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/60393215/" key="person_60393215">
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="standard" role="ant" change="#role-assignment">Kulaynī, Muḥammad ibn Yaʻqūb, d. 941?</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar" role="ant" change="#role-assignment">كليني، محمد بن يعقوب</persName>
                     </name>. Al-Kāfī, writen originally in Arabic, contains some 80 thousand traditions, divided into 33 books (for the titles see Ethe, 2667, p. 1451). The present Persian commentary, a response to the royal command, as stated in the preface, was commenced in the month of Rajab the year <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1659">1070</date>
                     <foreign xml:lang="fa">شروع شد در شرح کتاب یازدهم است بتاریخ رجب سال هزار و هفتاد هجری</foreign>, by then the commentator had already completed the first ten books of the Al-Kāfī the titles of which are given in the preface <locus from="1v" to="1v">1v</locus>
                     <foreign xml:lang="fa">کتاب العقل و کتاب التوحید و کتاب الحجه و کتاب الحجه و کتاب الایمان و الکفر و کتاب الدعا و کتاب فضل القرآن و کتاب العشرة و کتاب الجنایز</foreign> and at the end of this work he states that it would be followed by Kitāb al-Zakāt <foreign xml:lang="fa">این آخر کتاب الصلوة است از کتاب کافی از ابو جعفر کلینی... و در عقب آن می آید کتاب الزکوة قدوفق الشارح خلیل بن الغازی القزوینی...</foreign> The Persian commentary is divided into one hundred and three bāb <foreign xml:lang="fa">باب</foreign>
                  </summary>
